WEBVTT

00:00:01.300 --> 00:00:13.300
Jehovah God's inspired word makes this significant declaration at Titus, chapter 2, and verse 11.

00:00:13.300 --> 00:00:15.300
It reads,

00:00:15.300 --> 00:00:25.300
For the undeserved kindness of God has been manifested, bringing salvation to all sorts of people.

00:00:25.300 --> 00:00:29.300
Yes, to all sorts of people.

00:00:29.300 --> 00:00:35.299
This was true in the first century, and it's true today, more than ever before.

00:00:35.299 --> 00:00:43.299
We are a worldwide brotherhood made up of all sorts of people who have come to a knowledge of the truth,

00:00:43.299 --> 00:00:48.299
and we have made the decision to serve Jehovah.

00:00:48.299 --> 00:00:54.299
In this symposium, we will discuss three sorts of people.

00:00:54.299 --> 00:01:00.299
First, those whose mates are not yet Jehovah's Witnesses.

00:01:00.299 --> 00:01:07.299
Second, those who are being raised by one believing parent or relative.

00:01:07.299 --> 00:01:11.299
And third, those who are single.

00:01:11.299 --> 00:01:23.299
Many brothers and sisters who find themselves in these situations are successfully putting up a hard fight for the faith as stated in Jude, verse 3.

00:01:24.299 --> 00:01:29.299
And all of them are valuable assets to the congregation.

00:01:29.299 --> 00:01:43.299
So as we discuss each situation during this symposium, please focus your attention on those who are in the congregation that you attend and ask yourself.

00:01:43.299 --> 00:01:51.299
How can I show my appreciation for brothers and sisters who have these circumstances?

00:01:51.299 --> 00:02:05.640
And ask yourself, if I am in one of the situations being discussed, what will help me to continue to fight successfully for the faith?

00:02:05.640 --> 00:02:11.639
This talk will focus on Christians with unbelieving mates.

00:02:11.639 --> 00:02:20.639
For a well-known example, we look back to the first century to a woman named Eunice, the mother of Timothy.

00:02:20.639 --> 00:02:31.639
She is referred to in Acts 161, which says that Timothy was the son of a believing Jewish woman, but of a Greek father.

00:02:31.639 --> 00:02:35.639
So it refers to Eunice as a believing woman.

00:02:35.639 --> 00:02:40.639
But it does not refer to Timothy's father as a believing man.

00:02:40.639 --> 00:02:45.639
The point is that Timothy's father was not a Christian.

00:02:45.639 --> 00:02:59.400
Nevertheless, Eunice, his mother, along with Lois, his grandmother, taught Timothy the holy writings, the truth as found in God's Word.

00:02:59.400 --> 00:03:08.400
When we speak of unbelieving mates, we recognize that their circumstances are not all the same.

00:03:08.400 --> 00:03:12.400
Some non-witness mates oppose true worship.

00:03:12.400 --> 00:03:20.400
Others are indifferent, and others may be tolerant, even somewhat interested and supportive.

00:03:20.400 --> 00:03:25.400
But they may not be progressing toward baptism.

00:03:25.400 --> 00:03:32.400
Some mates of believers are baptized, but they have weakened spiritually.

00:03:32.400 --> 00:03:39.400
They may no longer be regular at meetings, go in service, or participate in family worship.

00:03:40.400 --> 00:03:50.400
And last of all, sad to say, some mates are disfellowshipped, but we never give up on unbelieving mates.

00:03:50.400 --> 00:04:02.449
And we always hope that any who are disfellowshipped will come to their senses, repent, and return to Jehovah.

00:04:02.449 --> 00:04:13.449
Is there something that we as publishers in the congregation can do to show appreciation for fellow believers whose mates are not yet serving Jehovah?

00:04:13.449 --> 00:04:27.449
Yes, there is. And the Apostle Paul tells us at Philippians chapter 3, verse 17, that we can learn from their good example and imitate them.

00:04:27.449 --> 00:04:31.449
Philippians chapter 3, verse 17 says,

00:04:32.449 --> 00:04:46.449
Unitedly, become imitators of me, brothers, and keep your eye on those who are walking in a way that is in harmony with the example we set for you.

00:04:46.449 --> 00:04:55.449
So Paul tells us to look closely at his example and the fine example of others in the congregation.

00:04:56.449 --> 00:05:02.449
Among those setting a fine example are brothers and sisters who have unbelieving mates.

00:05:02.449 --> 00:05:07.449
They have worked hard to maintain a strong relationship with Jehovah.

00:05:07.449 --> 00:05:13.449
They have cultivated self-discipline to keep a good schedule of theocratic activities,

00:05:13.449 --> 00:05:21.449
and many have become proficient in balancing family obligations with spiritual pursuits.

00:05:21.449 --> 00:05:27.449
It's not easy, but they are doing it.

00:05:27.449 --> 00:05:32.449
So how should we view them and treat them?

00:05:32.449 --> 00:05:37.449
We do what Philippians chapter 2, verse 4 tells us to do.

00:05:37.449 --> 00:05:44.449
We look out not only for our own interests, but also for the interests of others.

00:05:44.449 --> 00:05:48.449
That means that we show concern for their well-being.

00:05:48.449 --> 00:05:51.449
We treat them with respect.

00:05:51.449 --> 00:05:54.449
We certainly do not ignore them.

00:05:54.449 --> 00:06:01.449
We recognize that as spiritual people, they have much to offer.

00:06:01.449 --> 00:06:08.449
Isn't it wonderful that we are family and we belong to one another?

00:06:08.449 --> 00:06:13.449
We take brothers and sisters who have unbelieving mates into account,

00:06:13.449 --> 00:06:17.449
and we look out for their interests as the Scripture states,

00:06:17.449 --> 00:06:22.449
because we love them and we see their good qualities.

00:06:22.449 --> 00:06:27.449
So what can we do?

00:06:27.449 --> 00:06:32.449
Whenever possible, we should include them in our activities.

00:06:32.449 --> 00:06:36.449
But what else can we do?

00:06:36.449 --> 00:06:42.449
We can show interest in their mates and try to help them spiritually.

00:06:42.449 --> 00:06:51.449
For example, if circumstances allow, invite them with their mates for a meal or to a gathering.

00:06:51.449 --> 00:06:59.449
You know that friendliness and upbuilding conversation can have a powerful effect on a person's heart.

00:06:59.449 --> 00:07:08.449
As you watch the following video, think about how you can show appreciation for any in your congregation

00:07:08.449 --> 00:07:14.449
whose mates are not presently serving Jehovah.

