My husband was cooperative.

00:07:32.449 --> 00:07:36.449
He would wave goodbyes we went to the meetings.

00:07:36.449 --> 00:07:41.449
But he wasn't interested at all.

00:07:41.449 --> 00:07:47.449
I felt really jealous when I saw families sitting together at assemblies.

00:07:47.449 --> 00:07:52.699
Because of work and taking care of his mother,

00:07:52.699 --> 00:07:56.699
my husband gradually started missing meetings.

00:07:56.699 --> 00:08:01.699
Some in our congregation, with good intentions, pointed it out to him.

00:08:01.699 --> 00:08:07.699
But the way they did this made him feel misunderstood and discouraged.

00:08:07.699 --> 00:08:11.699
And he put the Bible and the publications away.

00:08:11.699 --> 00:08:19.839
I also had times when I wanted to drift away with him.

00:08:19.839 --> 00:08:23.839
I was really happy when I learned the truth.

00:08:23.839 --> 00:08:27.839
In my zeal, I bombarded my husband with information.

00:08:27.839 --> 00:08:30.839
And that made him worry that I had turned into a fanatic.

00:08:30.839 --> 00:08:36.090
I think he was genuinely concerned for his family.

00:08:36.090 --> 00:08:40.909
And thought that I had joined a weird religion.

00:08:40.909 --> 00:08:45.909
One family in the congregation often invited us to meals and outdoor activities.

00:08:45.909 --> 00:08:50.909
I think my husband appreciated those small acts of kindness.

00:08:50.909 --> 00:08:55.909
I also tried to show that I appreciated him through my speech and conduct.

00:08:55.909 --> 00:09:01.419
When my children and I applied what we learned in our lives,

00:09:01.419 --> 00:09:06.419
I think he gradually became interested in the truth.

00:09:06.419 --> 00:09:11.419
The words, safeguard your heart, caught my eye.

00:09:11.419 --> 00:09:19.419
I decided to try and keep my heart and my children's hearts towards Jehovah.

00:09:20.419 --> 00:09:23.419
When I went out in the ministry with my children,

00:09:23.419 --> 00:09:28.419
I would point out various aspects of God's creation around us.

00:09:28.419 --> 00:09:32.419
And before my husband would come home from work,

00:09:32.419 --> 00:09:36.419
I made it a habit to teach them God's word.

00:09:36.419 --> 00:09:42.419
I made a conscious effort to see myself in paradise with my husband.

00:09:42.419 --> 00:09:47.419
This strengthened my resolve to never leave the truth.

00:09:48.419 --> 00:09:53.419
I wrote caring notes to my husband when I went to the meetings.

00:09:53.419 --> 00:09:58.419
I was convinced that he would come back one day.

00:09:58.419 --> 00:10:01.419
And he did come back.

00:10:01.419 --> 00:10:08.419
I did not leave Jehovah and so Jehovah never abandoned me.

00:10:08.419 --> 00:10:12.419
My husband never embraced the truth.

00:10:12.419 --> 00:10:17.419
However, right now, all five of my children are in the truth.

00:10:17.419 --> 00:10:21.419
And I feel really blessed.

00:10:21.419 --> 00:10:26.419
Being able to serve Jehovah as a family, along with my husband,

00:10:26.419 --> 00:10:34.779
the joy and appreciation just keep dwelling up.

00:10:34.779 --> 00:10:37.779
What did we learn from the video?

00:10:37.779 --> 00:10:42.779
We learned that believing mates who display fine Christian qualities

00:10:42.779 --> 00:10:48.779
can have a positive influence on mates who are not yet serving Jehovah.

00:10:48.779 --> 00:10:54.779
So what will help you to keep on fighting for the faith?

00:10:54.779 --> 00:10:59.779
Wisdom and strength that only Jehovah can provide.

00:10:59.779 --> 00:11:03.779
Remember, his power is unlimited,

00:11:03.779 --> 00:11:09.779
and he finds pleasure in showing favor to those who trust in him.

00:11:10.779 --> 00:11:13.779
Also, you know that he loves you,

00:11:13.779 --> 00:11:21.019
